text: Anartia chrysopelea, the Cuban peacock or Caribbean peacock, is a species of butterfly generally only found in Cuba, although stray specimens have been encountered in Monroe County, Florida. ==References== ==External links== *Protein sequencing *"Anartia Hübner, [1819]" at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms Category:Anartia Category:Insects of Cuba Category:Endemic fauna of Cuba Category:Taxa named by Jacob Hübner Category:Butterflies described in 1831
title: Anartia chrysopelea
